From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 14:36:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 42/46] web-app: relay picker on instant onboarding from the
 chatmail relay directory
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The "create profile" onboarding screen shows a dropdown right above the
privacy-policy consent to pick the chatmail relay the new address is
created on: the default relay first, then the public relays fetched live
from the relay directory, filtered down to relays the WS→TCP bridge's
/dns endpoint can resolve — a relay the bridge can't resolve can't be
signed up on from this app.

The directory is JSON from chatmail-relays-mirror — a dumb automated
daily mirror of chatmail.at/relays (the site's markdown source repo is
private and the site sends no CORS headers, so a browser app can read
neither directly); it's the project's own repo, served with CORS from
GitHub raw. A small defensive JSON extractor ({relays:[{host}]}) takes
the valid hostnames and skips anything malformed, with a body-size cap
against a hostile source. The consent link follows the choice to the
picked relay's /privacy.html.

The dropdown only renders when there is a real choice: more than one
reachable relay, and no scanned dcaccount:/dclogin: QR pinning the
server. Everything fails soft — if the directory or the bridge is
unreachable, onboarding looks exactly like before. Styled
(styles.module.scss) to match the display-name input above it.

The source is configurable via SLOTHFUL_RELAY_DIRECTORY (baked into
window.__slothfulConfig.relayDirectoryUrl): unset = the default mirror,
a https URL = fetch there, "off" = no directory, the picker never
shows. The choice lives in InstantOnboardingContext so account creation
and the consent link always agree; a scanned account/login QR still
overrides everything.

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
